article.headline: Gardner-Webb 21, Presbyterian 14
article.story: CLINTON, S.C. -- Patrick Hall rushed for 114 yards and two touchdowns to lead Gardner-Webb to a 21-14 victory over Presbyterian in both teams' season finale on Saturday. Hall scored on a 2-yard run with 3:28 left in the first quarter to give Gardner-Webb (6-5, 3-3 Big South) a 7-0 lead, and darted 49 yards with 1:16 left in the game for a 21-7 lead. Presbyterian (0-11, 0-6 Big South) scored twice in the fourth quarter, including a 13-yard pass from Brandon Miley to Patrick McKoy with 50 seconds left, but couldn't recover the onside kick. Gardner-Webb dominated the first half, piling up 303 total yards, but needed a 4-yard pass from Stan Doolittle to Jamal Patmon with 30 seconds left to take a 14-0 lead into halftime. Doolittle was 25 of 36 for 273 yards, completing nine passes to James Perry, who finished with 133 yards. Miley was 19-for-34 for 247 yards.
